post_text:
Good afternoon everyone,

I am pleased to announce that starting tomorrow through the end of September, Henry County R-I has been approved to offer free breakfast and lunches to all children in our district through the age of 18. Once available, we will fill out required paperwork to try to get this extended through the end of the semester or when the funding runs out, whichever is sooner. If approved through the end of the semester, charges for meals will return to normal. If your child currently has a credit for meals, this will be held and then used once the program ends. If your child does not attend the district in person, and you would like to participate, contact Melissa Hall at (660) 647-3533 ext. 352. If you have any questions, please call me at (660) 647-3533.

Respectfully,

Scott Ireland
Superintendent of Schools
Henry County R-I

shared_text:
Windsor Youth Volleyball Association
August 20 at 2:37 PM ·

Practice begins Monday, Aug 24th!

At this time we only have two 4th graders signed up, and it is likely that we will not have a 4th grade team this year, but I will confirm that after sign ups close tomorrow.

5th Grade Practice-6-7:30

6th Grade Practice- 7:30-9

Girls will need to be in gym clothes, tennis shoes, knee pads, and will need their own water bottles. (If they don’t have knee pads yet that is ok)

PARENT MEETING: Monday Aug 24th-
This mandatory meeting will be held at 5:45 for 5th grade parents and 7:15 for 6th grade. You MUST be present in order for your child to practice on Monday. Please make sure to have your health insurance provider/policy number for the meeting.

We will discuss the upcoming season, restrictions, and all guidelines we will be following this year to protect our players and families.

$45 Registration will be due at the meeting as well.

Thank you!

Memo from the Superintendent,

Thank you once again for your patience while we determine the best way to proceed with the education of your children. We have posted the reentry plan as it stands today. This plan is subject to change and will be in accordance with CDC and Henry County Health Department regulations. I know there is much concern over this situation. We know you must make decisions you feel are best for your children. Hopefully, this plan will ease your minds as we move forward with educating the children of the Henry County R-1 School District. We have prepared an Enrollment Plan form as well. We must have a completed form for every child on file. This form is vital as we prepare for the instruction of our children. These forms can be completed on-line from our website or a hard copy can be picked up from the central office. If for any reason, you need to contact me, please do so at (660) 647-3533.

Respectfully,

Scott Ireland
Superintendent of Schools

Here are a few reminders since free sports physicals start today at Golden Valley Clinics.
*A physical is good for 2 years from the date your athlete last got one. If you're unsure of your child's last physical, log onto PRIVIT to check or just get a new one.
*If you need to get another physical, you need to upload your physical to PRIVIT, which serves as our storage system. There are hard copies of the instructions for uploading your physical at the district/superintendent's office at the high school.
*All incoming 7th graders wanting to participate in athletics will need to get a physical.

post_text: The Henry County R-1 School District is accepting applications for a (PK-6) elementary principal for the 2020-21 school year. Applicants must possess current Missouri certification as an Elementary Principal (PK-6) or be able to secure this before August 1, 2020. Interested candidates should submit a completed application packet which includes the following items: (1)A completed district application, (2) A letter of interest in the position, (3) A current resume, (4) A copy of all college transcripts and certificates and (5) A minimum of three(3)letters of reference. Applicants should contact Mr. Scott Ireland, Superintendent of Schools, at (660) 647-3533 or by email: irelands@henrycountyr1.k12.mo.us with specific questions regarding the vacancy.

post_text:
Message from OPAA food service director Melissa Hall:

Friday is Superhero day! Last Friday packets were sent out for you to complete for prizes. Please email those to me no later than tomorrow at 3 pm so you can possibly win a prize.

Kids are invited to wear their favorite Superhero Costume to come get their meals, OPAA will be wearing ours!!! We invite any staff that plan on helping to get involved as well or even parents coming to get the meals. Let’s make it fun!
OPAA will be placing a Superhero sticker in each meal bag. If a child gets a sticker with my name on the back they can trade the sticker for an ICE Cream Prize.
Three other ways to win:
2nd grade down - Design their own Superhero Cape (Winners receive Ice Cream)
3rd -5th grade - Design their own Superhero (Winners receive Ice Cream)
6th grade up - Write an essay about their "Real Life Superhero" winners will receive a gift card.

There will be extra prizes donated from Sonic, Dairy Queen as well as from Opaa!

Please email me your designs
Mhall@opaafood.com

Thanks everyone I look forward to seeing your creativity!

post_text:
Track runners, here is a post from Coach Eggers:

Conference is next week-if you have been training please leave your time on the track-there is chalk there. I have asked the Smithton coach about “virtual times”, he said he would ask some kids.
The great part of this social distancing is you have to see what you have inside yourself and self motivation. Now is the time for experimenting-what is the best time to run? What is your best snack (my best snack is a cookie 🍪 or peanut butter on a banana 🍌-worst is McDonalds 🤮)or meal the night before? Do your sprint repeats - which is fastest: first, second, or third? Try a slow jog recovery and do another sprint.

Get out the door-you will never regret a run when your done! ✅

Proud of you guys!!
Eggers

Starting Friday night on April 10th, WHS will be joining schools around the country by turning on our football stadium lights on Friday night at 8:20 p.m., which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them lit for 20 minutes, and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. We want all community members to be aware in the event someone is wondering why our stadium lights are on.

At 8:20 p.m. on Friday night look toward Windsor High School and David Powell Memorial Field to see the glow of our support for our graduating class of 2020.

Please, continue to follow CDC guidance and stay safe and healthy. We miss all of our students and staff.

post_text:
A post from Coach Eggers for our track distance runners:

HELLO😃 Long distance!!

Warm up

Monday-2 timed 4 minute runs

Tuesday-easy 1- 1 1/2 mile run

Wednesday -Repeats- shoot for 3-5, run either 400's or 800's or 1 mile or mix it up!!

Thursday-steady Indian drill - 1 mile. If not with anyone run from power line to power line fast
then easy, etc

Friday 1 mile hills, run 1/2 mile and 3-5 hills, and 1/2 mile cool down

Every day do sit ups, push ups, burpees or mt. climbers. Shoot for 30 each or
go crazy and knock out 50 each!!

Happy Running😃😃 From Eggers

And remember one day it will be Corona Virus NO more-a!!

A favorite Quote
"Some days it just flows and I feel like I'm born to do this, other days it feels like I'm trudging through he(double toothpicks). Every day I make the choice to SHOW UP and see what I've got, and to try and be better." Des Linden

post_text:
From the Superintendents Desk:

Area superintendents participated in a video conference meeting today with the Henry County Health Department. The health department stressed that if individuals are experiencing flu-like symptoms or upper respiratory symptoms that they should stay home. They also advised to not panic.
If individuals are feeling fine then go on with business as usual.

The HCR1 admin team and counselors will be meeting Monday to work on a plan for alternate instruction in the event the district has to cancel classes due to Covid 19.

The district will continue to communicate with the health department concerning best practice. Simply put, wash hands, if sick, stay home.

post_text:
District Lawn Care Advertisement

The Henry County R-I School District is seeking bids from Lawn care contractors to provide mowing for the district’s lawns. Needed services include Mow/edge/trim currently defined H.S. property including track/football field once weekly. Mow/edge/trim currently defined elementary property once weekly. The contract will include mowing football field/track complex in between mowings at no cost. Other areas added will be agreed to by both parties. The contractor must provide evidence they carry insurance for potential damages to district or employee property. The deadline for sealed bids is March 6, 2020, and will be opened during the regularly scheduled board meeting on March 9, 2020. The potential contract would begin April 2020. Questions may be directed to Mr. Dan Pruitt by calling 660-647-3533. The Henry County R-I School district is an equal opportunity employer.

post_text:
Preschool students have been learning about penguins for the last 3 weeks. They have learned so much and done lots of fun activities.
1) Students tobogganed down the hallway on scooters like penguins.
2) Students measured themselves next to a life size (4 ft tall) emperor penguin.
3). Students hid and sang a unique song like baby penguins do to help their parents find them.
4) Students decorated a pebble to give to someone special like male penguins give to female penguins.
5) Students carefully transferred eggs to each other like mommy penguins must do to daddy penguins.
6) Students ate snow cones to show how penguins must eat snow and ice to stay hydrated.

post_text: The Henry County R-I School district is seeking applicants for a part-time Health Clerk. This position will offer four hours per day for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Pay will start at $8.90 per hour with the possibility of increased pay with experience and certification. Certification or medical experience is preferred. Benefits paid will be social security and Medicare. Health insurance will not be offered. Interested applicants may contact Dr. Shawn Schultz for a job description or application by phone: 660-647-3533 or email: schultzs@henrycountyr1.k12.mo.us. The deadline for applications will be February 3rd, 2020. The HCR1 school district is an equal opportunity employer.

post_text: Your WHS Academic Team played well again at the meet at Lincoln yesterday, 12/10/19. They won their game against Northwest 340 to 80 and won against Stover 230 to 160. They suffered their first loss to Cole Camp 330 to 140. Team captain Adam Warlen once again led in scoring, but the other team members: Christopher Adams, Mirranda Himmelberg, Cayleb Swindell, and Rose Moser contributed.
